<br>
I keep hearing different things about chr being very important to it being inconsequential when it's over 100-150.  Does anyone know if this is indeed true?  Am I wasting my time switching out chr gear for int?  Should I load up on chr gear, or just go with int??  Any help would be greatly appreciated!  <br>
<br>
Destinny of Drinal <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/uyadensamsara.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yaden Samsara</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#330000>(2/15/01 1:31:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=55.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://blackhole.cs.uwec.edu/~krauspa/claudus.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How Effective is Raising Chr in Mezzing?!?</span><hr size=1> Most of what I have seen shows CHA does help out on mezzing. I am trying to get mine up as much as possible. <p><hr><center><img src="http://blackhole.cs.uwec.edu/~krauspa/yaden.jpg"><BR><B><I>Yaden Samsara</B> Enchanter 34</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/uchere.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Chere</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://home.earthlink.net/~tasha_chere/_uimages/smiley.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#330000>(2/27/01 5:30:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=55.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~tasha_chere/_uimages/chereface.GIF WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How Effective is Raising Chr in Mezzing?!?</span><hr size=1> It seems critical to have it above 160, but I have both my int and cha close to 200.  <br>
<br>
*hugs*<br>
<br>
 <p><img src="http://home.earthlink.net/~tasha_chere/_uimages/orgchere.gif"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/udellenneq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dellenn EQ</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eyes.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#330000>(3/5/01 8:49:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=55.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.facelink.com/Dellenn?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How Effective is Raising Chr in Mezzing?!?</span><hr size=1> If I'm in a situation where the mobs seem to be resisting mez a lot more than usual I put on some extra CHA gear that I carry around with me which almost brings it up to around 195ish and I notice a dramatic decrease in resists.  If I know I'm going to be doing mainly crowd control rather than buffing (which is more often true than not at this level) I make sure I have that extra CHA. <p>Dellenn<BR>
42nd Dark Elf Enchanter<BR>
Blades of Law, Povar<BR>
<BR>
"Much suspected by me,<BR>
Nothing proved can be."<BR>
    -Elizabeth I</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/ulearith.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Learith</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#330000>(3/14/01 2:45:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=55.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How Effective is Raising Chr in Mezzing?!?</span><hr size=1> Charisma is quite important in mezzing.. I have my charisma around 230 and int around 200 buffed..trying to get them as high as possible...usually in old sebilis. At level 56 you get a +50 charisma spell. there have been times when I've noticed that things are resisting way too much in old sebilis..like 2-3 times in a row and the reason is because I don't have that spell on. Once you raise charisma you see a dramatic difference. Quite important.<br>
<br>
Learith<br>
56 enchanter - Fennin <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/uburien.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Burien</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#330000>(3/20/01 7:06:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=55.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How Effective is Raising Chr in Mezzing?!?</span><hr size=1> eternal debate over int over charisma, and just how much does charisma help, honestly....<br>
im of the charisma over int school myself, there is a cap of 200 on int, BUT not a cap on charisma (this is for benefits of points), keeping your charisma maxxed will make your charms/mezzes hit better and (hopefully on charms) longer.  i personally keep my charisma at 237 or so at all times, sacrificing ac for it, but in the long run i think its so worth it.  my 2 cents<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/udestinny.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Destinny</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#330000>(4/1/01 9:14:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=55.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How Effective is Raising Chr in Mezzing?!?</span><hr size=1> Ok, I'm level 27.  Does level factor into the need for higher chr at this level?  I'm just wondering if I should sacrafice int for chr at this level.<br>
<br>
