<br>
Just checking...and is there any truth to belief that if you can get your stat to new level (100, 150, 200, 250)?<br>
<br>
Thanks,<br>
Destinny <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/uyadensamsara.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yaden Samsara</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 31<br> <font color=#330000>(4/1/01 10:09:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=55.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How Effective is Raising Chr in Mezzing?!?</span><hr size=1> I know a lot of games do stats by round numbers in order to see improvement. It wouldn't surprise me if their were levels or improvement at steps like 100, 150 and 200, and very little change inbetween. Of course with Verant, who knows... /sigh <p><hr><center><img src="http://blackhole.cs.uwec.edu/~krauspa/itchy.gif"><BR><B><I><font color="blue"><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=45675">Yaden Samsara</a></font> Order of Courage</B> Enchanter 47<br><I>"were just a speck of dirt on this golf ball
called earth, so get stupid and sing" -- 311</i><center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/utimhenchanter.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Timh Enchanter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#330000>(4/6/01 3:37:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=55.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How Effective is Raising Chr in Mezzing?!?</span><hr size=1> my 2 copper:<br>
<br>
I WISH that charisma would make a difference, but it seems like the difference is either non existant or very little<br>
<br>
Charisma helps nothing noticeable with mez. Why would it help? less resists? mez lasting longer?<br>
No. The spells won't last longer because they have a set time. And I doubt charisma lowers the chance to resist mez.<br>
<br>
I've not noticed any difference having 85 charisma, 100, 120, 150, 160, 170. No difference, no matter what charisma I have.<br>
<br>
The same goes for Charm!<br>
I have had stuff charmed for a long time at 85 charisma, and at 170, and I've had the charm break within 1 second at both 85 and 170 charisma.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/uikitclaw.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ikitclaw</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#330000>(4/6/01 4:39:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=55.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How Effective is Raising Chr in Mezzing?!?</span><hr size=1> HEAR HEAR !!!  Having carried my various charisma items with me all the time.. and constantly switching my setup for the current situation... I too feel the same..  For mezs..  cha just doesnt seem to matter.. altho i do notice an alarming number of resists with the lower lvl mobs when cha is lower than 100..  I really do not see much difference when hunting in seb when i have a 100 cha  or a 200....<br>
54th enchanter of aya ro <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/uyadensamsara.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yaden Samsara</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 33<br> <font color=#330000>(4/6/01 4:57:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=55.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How Effective is Raising Chr in Mezzing?!?</span><hr size=1> Of all the things in this game I wish I knew, this is definitely up there on the list. <p><hr><center><B><I><font color="blue"><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=45675">Yaden Samsara</a></font> Order of Courage</B> Enchanter 48<br><I>"who needs actions when you've got words"</i><center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/ujimatra.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jimatra</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#330000>(4/30/01 9:23:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=55.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.cvzoom.net/~shireman/lebowski.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How Effective is Raising Chr in Mezzing?!?</span><hr size=1> I have a buffed CHA in excess of 200 and I notice I have markedly better results with it over the 200 mark.   <p>The Reverend Jimatra Jericho - Level 5-0 Uberchanter and Pimp Daddy<br>
Jimz0r - Level 8 Monky Brawler<br>
Officer, Veeshan Guard<br>
"Ain't nobody dope as me... ~Outkast"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/ugoanad.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Goanad</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#330000>(5/3/01 4:54:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=55.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How Effective is Raising Chr in Mezzing?!?</span><hr size=1> I have to wonder, aloud for the moment, how such a profound difference can exist between your perceptions and those of the initial posters in this thread??  Was your resisted mezzed or charms simply untimely or did you do some kind of trial where X number of tests where conducted with Y resists at different levels of CHA????   <br>
<br>
There's just too much of a gulf between the sides in this debate....something is amiss.<br>
<br>
MookDaddy<br>
16th Chanter <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/uyadensamsara.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yaden Samsara</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#330000>(5/3/01 8:06:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=55.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://blackhole.cs.uwec.edu/~krauspa/alive.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How Effective is Raising Chr in Mezzing?!?</span><hr size=1> That is one reason I don't put too much faith into player run tests.<br>
<br>
