Cleerthought Fiverplat Chanter of the 45th season =) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/uslymie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>slymie</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_magentaspot.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#330000>(5/8/01 12:32:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=55.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How Effective is Raising Chr in Mezzing?!?</span><hr size=1> Well I have been reading conflicting posts on the Cha over Int issue since, ummmm about the third week EQ came out. Here is my stance on it. Cha helps with charm, that I would say pretty much everyone agrees on. Although there are some out there that still refute even this. I personally always keep charm memmed as my end all of crowd control. In that light I have been working at keping my int and cha BOTH as high as I can. Being a human I was able to start both out at 100,a nd now, at level 50, I have a nice Cha of 194 buffed and Int of 188.<br>
<br>
So my advice: keep em both up. Higher cha helps as does higher int. If you do you job properly you should rarely run out of mana, unless it the train from hell. A decent cha helps spells stick, and a decent int ensures you have mana for the spells you need to cast.<br>
<br>
Thats just my 2 coppers. No indepth tests, no number crunching, just the way it seems to work for me. <p>Slymie Ras <br>
