<br>
Myself, *I* see enough of a difference when I dont have my handy +cha buff up that its noticable. from most records a Cha over 175 seems to be good for anything involving Mes'ing. Personally, I keep Cha up to 190ish normally now and use the spare rings/earrings/shield/belt for +hp gear <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
It does seem to depend largely on what level you are, and what level the mob you are trying to mes is. If you're trying to mes a red/yellow with 120cha.. you're toast in most cases.. but with 240, you have a reasonable chance of sticking it. but if you're playing mostly with low blue froggies in sebilis, you can go in with a cha of 100 and do perfectly fine.. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
