<br>
Some days I can stick an AE mez on three onrushing reds, and some days the low blue tashed resists three mezzes and half my stuns.... like the plaguebone skeleton in COM the other day. Tash. mez. chain stun. ow ow ow. mez. ow ow ow. chain stun. ow ow ow. mez. ow ow ow. baby stun hits, immobilize back off. Meanwhile my healers are going out of their mind watching my hp bar bounce up and down as the gheal lands and the skele duals me for 86 or something.<br>
<br>
I have about 161 int and 160 cha with usual gear and buffs.<br>
<br>
I do put on that cha, though, because in close situations, more so than other classes, a resisted spell can make things very nasty very quickly. I put on some extra int gear after I got my level 34 spells and some of my skills ~* cough evoke *~ were rather low and I was fizzling way too much. After I kicked my int up to 155 or something, it didn't happen nearly as much. <br>
<br>
I hardly have a problem with mana anyway. Crowd control is cheap. I can turn a certain death heavy pull into orderly slaughter on 20 or 30m. I can't remember the last time I died because I went OOM in a group situation. I think it was very close once in recent memory, but the necro twitched me because we still had two or three mezzed mobs to kill and the time on the current mez was running out.<br>
<br>
As to charm, I don't use it for crowd control that much. It tends to confuse/piss off the other group members... so cha doesn't matter much to me there. I charm soloed portions of various levels, which can be lots of fun and very rewarding, but charm seems to have a mind of it's own. Charm line doesn't get *outright resisted* much, but I've had crappy two tick charms all the time on loser mobs, and have it stick on a even for 7 kills, one after the other.<br>
